HTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.startupsfortherestofus.com/\">Startups for the rest of us</a></strong></p>\n<p>Started in 2010 by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/robwalling\">Rob Walling</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SingleFounder\">Mike Taber</a> have covered almost everything there is to cover in micropreneurship. <a href=\"http://www.startupsfortherestofus.com/greatest-hits\">Here</a> you can find a 'best of' selection of their podcast.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T16:55:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Podcasts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://thesaasbootstrapper.com/\">The SaaS Bootstrapper</a></strong></p>\n<p>Interviews with entrepreneurs and bootstrappers about bootstrapping, SaaS, growth, marketing, and other startup topics. By <a href=\"http://macmartine.com/\">Mac Martine</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T16:55:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Podcasts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.smartpassiveincome.com/podcasts/\">Smart Passive Income</a></strong></p>\n<p>Not really specific to developers but with great content on the several types of products to make a living online. By <a href=\"https://twitter.com/patflynn\">Pat Flynn</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T16:55:06.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"unixorn/awesome-zsh-plugins","categoryHTML":"<h2>Plugins</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/micrenda/zsh-nohup\">nohup</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/micrenda/zsh-nohup\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5,\"repo\":\"micrenda/zsh-nohup\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Add <code>nohup</code> to the current command pressing <code>Ctrl-H</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T16:35:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Newsletters</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.indiehackers.com/businesses\">IndieHackers</a></strong></p>\n<p>Newsletter containing the newest interviews of the site and also the best threads from the forum. Normally ships on Thursdays. By <a href=\"https://twitter.com/csallen?lang=ca\">Courtland Allen</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T15:49:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Newsletters</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://justinjackson.ca/indie/\">Indie</a></strong></p>\n<p>Stories, lessons, and inspiration for independent makers. By <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mijustin\">Justin Jackson</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T15:49:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Podcasts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.productpeople.tv/\">Product People</a></strong></p>\n<p>A podcast focused on great products and the people who make them. Since 2012. By <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mijustin\">Justin Jackson</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T15:49:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Podcasts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://bootstrapped.fm/\">bootstrapped.fm</a></strong></p>\n<p>Several different topics around bootstrapping online businesses. Started in 2013 by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ianlandsman\">Ian Landsman</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/andrey_butov\">Andrey Butov</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T15:49:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Podcasts</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.indiehackers.com/businesses\">IndieHackers</a></strong></p>\n<p>Podcast where <a href=\"https://twitter.com/csallen?lang=ca\">Courtland Allen</a> interviews some of the most successful indiehackers featured on the site. Started in early 2017 already has 12 episodes with great content and very carefully crafted related notes and links.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T15:49:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sjfricke/awesome-webgl","categoryHTML":"<h2>WebGL</h2><h3>Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/tsherif/webgl2examples\">WebGL 2 Examples</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/tsherif/webgl2examples\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">363</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":363,\"repo\":\"tsherif/webgl2examples\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Rendering algorithms implemented in raw WebGL 2.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T12:51:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Communities</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://barnacl.es/\">Barnacl.es</a></strong></p>\n<p>News for bootstrappers, not VC hackers. Hacker-News like forum. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/pushcx\">Peter Bhat Harkins</a> started it in early 2016 and I've found it of great value ever since. Also, it runs on <a href=\"https://github.com/jcs/lobsters\">great software</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jcs/lobsters\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":4,\"repo\":\"jcs/lobsters\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->, which is always a thing to appreciate!</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T10:59:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Communities</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://discuss.bootstrapped.fm/\">bootstrapped.fm Forum</a></strong></p>\n<p>A forum for bootstrappers. Started in 2013 by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ianlandsman\">Ian Landsman</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/andrey_butov\">Andrey Butov</a> as a continuation to the now defunct <a href=\"http://discuss.joelonsoftware.com/default.asp?biz\">The Business of Software</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T10:59:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Communities</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/\">HackerNews</a></strong></p>\n<p>News for hackers, mostly technology and entrepreneurship. Not specific to indie devs but a must for everyone interested in computer science, creating products and making money. A lot of indie devs lurking around. Started by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/paulg\">Paul Graham</a> and maintained by the seed accelerator YCombinator.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T10:59:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mezod/awesome-indie","categoryHTML":"<h3>Communities</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.indiehackers.com/businesses\">IndieHackers</a></strong></p>\n<p>Learn from profitable businesses and side projects. IndieHackers is probably the catalyst for this new wave of interest on making an independent income. It is a collection of interviews to successful developers about their products. IndieHackers has been especially interesting to follow since it's been an indie project itself. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/csallen?lang=ca\">Courtland Allen</a> has been very transparent about <a href=\"https://www.indiehackers.com/blog\">how he built it</a>. The last news make one think that the forum/community will grow.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-04T10:58:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"faroit/awesome-python-scientific-audio","categoryHTML":"<h2>Audio Related Packages</h2><h4>Source Separation</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/stitchfix/NTFLib\">NTFLib</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/stitchfix/NTFLib\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">44</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":44,\"repo\":\"stitchfix/NTFLib\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> <a href=\"https://github.com/stitchfix/NTFLib\">:octocat:</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/stitchfix/NTFLib\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4p